The intended specific target market for the Official Police was mainly law enforcement agencies and it became one of the best selling police firearms of all time, eventually in the 1950s coming to exemplify typical peace officer weaponry.  The Official Police was also used by various U.S. and allied military forces during World War II.

title: For Sale:  EAA Windicator 4" Blued
postcontent: Up for sale I have an EAA Windicator .38 Special/.357 Magnum with a blued 4" barrel.Overall this gun is a pretty good gun.  Yes, it's heavy.  Yes, the trigger is heavy too.  But it has an excellent grip, and it's possibly one of the most accurate pistols I've shot before.  I once was at a range and I hit a water bottle at 80 yards.  Yes, 80 yards.  It was the most impressive shot I've ever taken, but I've also never even attempted to do better.One problem:  it shoots excellently in double action, besides the whole trigger being heavy thing.  But it has this weird issue where you can't pull back the hammer in single action unless you just feather the trigger, and this issue only happens about half the time, and the gun is still reliable in double action incase you need it for like hog hunting or defense.  I think it simply probably just needs an internal part cleaned or filed down, but I'm not really in the mood to mess with it myself.  For this reason I'm listing it well below value.I'm including a case with this.
